"'''Regina Cayli'''" is a solitaire adventure for ''[[Star Wars: The Roleplaying Game]]'' written by [[Ken Rolston]]. It was originally published in [[Star Wars: The Roleplaying Game (first edition)|''Star Wars: The Roleplaying Game'']] in [[October]] [[1987]] and later reprinted in [[Star Wars Adventure Journal 1|''Star Wars Adventure Journal 1'']] in [[February]] [[1994]], both by [[West End Games]].

In the adventure, the player assumes the role of the [[Smuggler/Legends|smuggler]] [[Roark Garnet/Legends|Roark Garnet]], who is in the process of trying to spring his [[Pilot/Legends|co-pilot]] from confinement aboard the [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Imperial]] [[Starship/Legends|vessel]] ''[[Regina Cayli]]'', from which the adventure gets its name.

==Plot summary==
[[Smuggler/Legends|Smugglers]] [[Roark Garnet/Legends|Roark Garnet]] and [[Hawk Carrow]] are forced down on [[New Bakstre]] by [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Imperial]] [[Imperial Office of Customs/Legends|Customs]] [[Starship/Legends|vessels]]. Their ship, the ''[[Dorion Discus]]'' crashed in the [[Forest/Legends|forest]] and an Imperial team wounds and captures Carrow. Garnet undertakes a daring rescue by sneaking aboard the [[M-Class Imperial Attack Transport]] ''[[Regina Cayli]]'' to liberate his friend and co-[[Pilot/Legends|pilot]].

